      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The Universal Classifier: go3"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "In English, we say 'one person' or 'two books'. In Cantonese, you can't just put a number in front of a noun. You need a <strong>Classifier</strong> (also called a measure word) in the middle."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The most common classifier is <strong>個</strong> (go3). It is used for people and many other general objects. The basic structure is: <br><strong>Number + Classifier + Noun</strong>"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "一個",
          "romanization": "jat1 go3",
          "translation": "One (of something)"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "一個人",
          "romanization": "jat1 go3 jan4",
          "translation": "One person"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "貴公司",
          "romanization": "gwai3 gung1 si1",
          "translation": "Your company (Formal)"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "位",
          "romanization": "wai2",
          "translation": "Classifier for people (Polite)"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "員工",
          "romanization": "jyun4 gung1",
          "translation": "Employee"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "type": "reading", "exerciseId": "4.2.2" },
